# Session 004 – Family

**Date:** 2026-07-13

**Sprint:** Sprint 0 – Product Discovery

## Goal

Define and approve the Family concept in the Product Model.

---

## Decisions

### Family approved

The Family concept is now approved.

A Family represents the people who share everyday life with one or more dogs.

---

### Family contains

- One or more people
- One or more dogs
- Shared goals
- Shared history
- Shared settings

---

### Person

DailyPaws may know:

- Name
- Experience with dogs
- Time spent with the dog
- Preferred activities
- Personal goals
- One or more roles

---

### Roles

Roles describe how a person participates in the dog's life.

Examples include:

- Primary Caregiver
- Adventure Buddy
- Play Partner
- Trick Trainer
- Calm Companion
- Walking Partner

A person may have multiple roles.

Roles may change over time.

---

### Relationships

Relationships are NOT part of the Family concept.

Every Person has one separate Relationship with every Dog.

The Relationship model will be defined later.

---

### Multiple dogs

The Product Model supports multiple dogs.

The MVP will initially support one dog per family.

---

## Working agreements

The team adopted a new way of working.

- One session = one decision.
- Documentation before implementation.
- New ideas go to the Parking Lot.
- Finish one concept before starting the next.
- Product Model concepts are approved one at a time.

---

## Outcome

✅ Family approved.

